The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Dec. 13: Maruti Udyog will raise prices by up to Rs 12,000 from January across its models. The company, which had last raised prices in August, has decided to go in for another revision because of increase in freight and input costs and informed its dealers about it. In the letters to its dealers, it has not disclosed the exact quantum of price increase each model will attract.

 Mumbai, Dec. 13: Raymond has entered into a joint venture agreement with US-based Aj Rose to set up a manufacturing facility in India with an initial investment of Rs 16.6 crore.

 Calcutta, Dec. 13: Allahabad Banks proposed joint venture with Punjab National Bank (PNB) to set up a banking subsidiary in Kazakhstan has been put on hold. Bank sources said there was no progress so far regarding the formation of the venture.

 New Delhi, Dec. 13: Zee Telefilms demerged shares, after hiving off the news and cable businesses, will start trading on the stock exchanges from December 18 while the new entities will be listed in January.

 Mumbai, Dec. 13: The South African arm of VSNL, Neotel, will raise a Rs 1,300-crore short-term loan, the largest funding for a start-up telecommunications project in that country, from a consortium of financial institutions.




